What you need to know:

Protests that began 12 days ago over abuses by the police's loathed Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) have spiralled dramatically.Some 18 people have died in the demonstrations as clashes have been reported between protesters and assailants wearing civilian clothes.Lagos, a city of 20 million, has been paralysed as crowds have blocked key roads and access to the international airport.Â 